{"key":"post-10153987","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10153987</id>\n<content>Like rotten apples, all it takes is one to spoil the whole batch.&amp;nbsp; Next time, don't waste your spores on a silly LC.&amp;nbsp; New growers push those, but you won't find many experienced growers ever recommending it.&amp;nbsp; Sugar water favors bacteria, and you never know if it's good or not unless you have a microscope until your jars fail, and then you've lost a month or more.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you want to move up, make petri dishes and test your spores on agar, and then when you have a clean culture, use it to inoculate your grains.&amp;nbsp; That way, you KNOW you have a good culture going.&amp;nbsp; However, you should still sniff each and every jar before use.&amp;nbsp; I do.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10155656</next>\n<prev>10153869</prev>\n<first>10149974</first>\n<last>10155656</last>\n<when>1239585806</when>\n<utime>04/13/09 04:23 AM</utime>\n</post>"}